Astrea of the Stars 14-Aug-21 06:45 PM
Honestly, it's more of a closet than it is a room. The room isn't too big - certainly bigger than a typical closet, but just about the size of a typical American bedroom. The dim lights and the tall cabinets and shelves here help to make this place feel much smaller, though. Walling through the narrow passageways, you can see a variety of cabinets, each labeled with a specific item. For example, the cabinet labeled 'Knives' has all sorts of knives in it, the cabinet labeled 'Lighters' has lighters... wait, this is just murder central, isn't it? Yep, everything in here has been put for murder usages. What's actually in here is hard to describe, but if it's typically used in murder (besides for medicines, poisons, and guns), it's probably in here (you can always DM me to ask). So it was purposely rigged to be like this, huh? Talia really must want you to murder. But... it makes you question: why? Why does she go this far? Is it really worth this? Guess there's no simple way of answering that. (edited)
